{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"assign","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"double","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:d"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"tileLodZoomShift"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Shift applied to the Zoom level during LOD calculation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A negative value shifts the Zoom level to a coarser level reducing quality but improving"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"performance A positive value shifts the Zoom level to a finer level increasing details but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"negatively affecting performance A value of zero (default) does not apply any shift to the Zoom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level It is not recommended to change the default value unless performance is critical and the loss"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of quality is acceptable. A value of -1 reduces the number of displayed tiles by a factor of 4 on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"average It is recommended to first configure the pixelRatio before adjusting TileLodZoomShift."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/tilelodzoomshift"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Camera based tile level of detail controls","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/tileLodZoomShift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\